Summary
-------

This summary is not a substitute for the license terms below.

You may:

- use Beeroniza personally, internally, or in your business;
- use Beeroniza to create images, websites, publications, customer work,
  marketing materials, or other commercial outputs;
- copy, modify, self-host, and redistribute Beeroniza under these terms.

You may not:

- sell, rent, lease, license, sublicense, or resell Beeroniza itself;
- charge for access to Beeroniza or a modified version of Beeroniza;
- offer Beeroniza as a paid hosted service, managed service, SaaS, API
  service, paid on-demand image-generation service, or commercial
  image-generation/template platform;
- offer a product or service whose value derives entirely or substantially
  from Beeroniza itself.

License Terms
-------------

1. Base License

Subject to the Beeroniza No-Sell Condition below, Beeroniza is licensed under
the Apache License, Version 2.0, reproduced below.

2. Beeroniza No-Sell Condition

The licenses granted under the Apache License, Version 2.0 do not include the
right to Sell Beeroniza.

"Sell Beeroniza" means exercising any rights granted under the Apache License,
Version 2.0 to provide Beeroniza, a modified version of Beeroniza, or a product
or service whose value derives entirely or substantially from the functionality
of Beeroniza, to third parties for a fee or other consideration.

This includes, without limitation, offering Beeroniza or a modified version of
Beeroniza as a paid software product, paid hosted service, paid managed service,
paid SaaS offering, paid API service, subscription service, reseller offering,
commercial distribution, rental, lease, license, or sublicense.

This also includes, without limitation, charging third parties to access or use
an on-demand image-generation, template-rendering, or output-generation workflow
whose value derives entirely or substantially from Beeroniza.

2.1 Safe Harbors

For the avoidance of doubt, the following do NOT constitute "Sell Beeroniza":

(a) providing support, consulting, training, or integration services relating to
Beeroniza, provided that Beeroniza itself is not the product being sold;

(b) building and operating a product in which Beeroniza is one non-primary
component alongside substantial other original functionality, such that the
commercial value of the offering does not derive primarily from Beeroniza;

(c) self-hosting Beeroniza for an organization's own internal operations,
including generating outputs for the organization's own websites, publications,
marketing, products, or broader client deliverables, provided that the
organization does not give customers or other third parties access to Beeroniza
or to an API, workflow, or self-service interface that exposes Beeroniza's image
or template generation as the paid product or service.

3. Permitted Business Use

For clarity, the Beeroniza No-Sell Condition does not prevent you from using
Beeroniza in your business or from charging for broader products, services,
content, images, publications, websites, applications, consulting work, or
customer deliverables created with Beeroniza as an internal tool, provided that
you do not Sell Beeroniza.

4. Outputs

Images and other outputs generated with Beeroniza are not subject to this
license merely because they were generated with Beeroniza. You are responsible
for any third-party rights in your input materials, templates, fonts, images,
logos, and other content.

5. Third-Party Components

Third-party dependencies, fonts, and other components included with or used by
Beeroniza remain under their own licenses. See NOTICE,
THIRD_PARTY_LICENSES.md, and THIRD_PARTY_NOTICES.txt for additional
information. THIRD_PARTY_NOTICES.txt is generated at build time and included in
distributed container images; it is not present in the source repository.
It contains the NOTICE files of Apache-2.0-licensed dependencies as required
by that license.

6. Trademarks

This license does not grant permission to use the names, trademarks, service
marks, or logos of any Beeroniza copyright holder, contributor, or affiliated
entity, except as required for reasonable and customary attribution.

